3.00	Multi-cultural	Multiculturalism	Multiculturalism is an ideology that promotes the institutionalisation of communities containing multiple cultures. It is generally applied to the demographic make-up of a specific place, usually at the organizational level, e.g. schools, businesses, neighborhoods, cities, or nations.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/Reach_Toronto.jpg/300px-Reach_Toronto.jpg
